      "workId": "solo-baseline-doc-improvement",
      "status": "complete",
      "title": "Add per-arm minimum board-row expectations to the task packet",
      "body": "Evidence inspected: only this task packet (Experiment goal, Current harness shape, Known measurement risks, Task, Output contract).\n\nRecommendation: extend the packet with a short 'Per-arm board-row expectations' section that names the minimum durable rows each arm must publish so the scorer can compare arms on board evidence alone:\n- single: coordination.final only.\n- orchestrator: >=1 coordination.work row (assignment) + coordination.final.\n- choreography: >=1 coordination.claims + >=1 coordination.findings (or coordination.reviews) + coordination.final.\n\nWhy it is enough: the packet already names the third measurement risk ('choreography should be judged by durable board behavior, not by hidden driver state') but the Output contract only mandates coordination.final. That asymmetry lets an orchestrator or choreography arm pass scoring with the same artifact a solo arm produces, erasing the very signal the experiment exists to measure. A few lines pinned to the contract close the gap without changing the harness or channels.\n\nOpen questions:\n- Should reviews be required for choreography or only when disagreement arises?\n- Should the orchestrator arm publish a coordination.questions row when delegating, to make 'central coordination' visible vs a single work row?\n- Is a row-count threshold (>=1) enough, or should the scorer also require distinct claimantSessionId values to distinguish real peer choreography from a solo agent emitting peer-shaped rows?",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-25T02:29:01.939Z"
    }
  },
